      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Introduction to Asking 'What is this?' (Masculine)",
          "arabic": "مقدمة: السؤال 'ما هذا؟'"
        },
        "text": "To ask 'What is this?' about a masculine object in Arabic, we use the phrase 'ما هذا؟'. 'ما' means 'what', and 'هذا' is the masculine demonstrative pronoun for 'this'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "ما هذا؟",
            "english": "What is this?",
            "transliteration": "Maa haadhā?"
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "ما هذا؟"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Vocabulary: Book (Masculine)",
          "arabic": "مفردات: كتاب"
        },
        "text": "Let's learn our first classroom object: 'book'. In Arabic, 'book' is 'كتاب', which is a masculine noun. When answering 'What is this?', we combine 'هذا' with the noun.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "كتاب",
            "english": "Book",
            "transliteration": "kitāb"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "هذا كتاب.",
            "english": "This is a book.",
            "transliteration": "Haadhā kitāb."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "كتاب. هذا كتاب."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
