      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking 'Is this a...?' (Masculine) with 'هل'",
          "arabic": "السؤال 'هل هذا...؟' (لمذكر)"
        },
        "text": "To ask a yes/no question like 'Is this a book?', we use 'هل' at the beginning of the sentence. 'هل' means 'is/are/do/does'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "هل هذا كتاب؟",
            "english": "Is this a book?",
            "transliteration": "Hal haadhā kitāb?"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "نعم، هذا كتاب.",
            "english": "Yes, this is a book.",
            "transliteration": "Naʿam, haadhā kitāb."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "لا، هذا ليس كتاباً.",
            "english": "No, this is not a book.",
            "transliteration": "Lā, haadhā laysa kitāban."
          }
        ],
        "audioText": "هل هذا كتاب؟ نعم، هذا كتاب. لا، هذا ليس كتاباً."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
